=====
What we're doing
Neither Monica nor I can hike every weekend so we are looking for ways to keep our legs and lungs in shape between our mountain adventures. The plan is to ride at least once a week this summer - and  this week we will be riding along the Nashua River Rail Trail.
The Nashua River Rail Trail is a former railroad right of way that travels about 12 miles from end-to-end through the MA towns of Ayer, Groton, Pepperell and Dunstable and enters into Nashua, NH. It offers a 10-foot wide paved surface for the entire length and travels along a varied landscape, offering numerous scenic overlooks, opportunities to see wildlife and several resting stops.
=====
Trip Summary
The objective is to ride at about a 15 MPH pace. There will be two options for this trip – an 8 mile round trip and a 24 mile round trip. Both options end near Charlotte’s Cozy Kitchen so you can finish the night off with an ice cream.
We will start at the eight-mile mark of the overall route and head north to Nashua before returning to the lot. If about eight miles is enough for you then you can end your trip here. The rest of us will continue south towards Ayer before returning to the lot. This should be about 24 miles round trip.
While I have been on this trail many times before I did all of my current research for this trip using the Internet. You should become familiar with this information since you are ultimately responsible for your own safety.

